Package: vellumverse
Title: Easily Install and Load the 'Vellum' Graphics Ecosystem
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R:
    person("David", "Schoch", , "david.schoch@cynkra.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The 'vellum' ecosystem is a set of packages for drawing in R
    that share a scene model and a common design: 'vellum' (a low-level
    graphics backend with a Rust engine), 'vellumplot' (a pipe-first grammar of
    graphics on top of it), and 'vellumwidget' (client-side interactive HTML
    widgets for the scenes they produce). 'vellumverse' is a meta-package
    that installs and loads them together, in the spirit of the
    'tidyverse'.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://r-vellum.github.io/vellumverse/,
    https://github.com/r-vellum/vellumverse,
    https://schochastics.r-universe.dev/vellumverse
BugReports: https://github.com/r-vellum/vellumverse/issues
